\begin_layout Standard
The purpose of this note is to illustrate the properties of the most recent
 version of MAKRO to a series of shocks.
 The model is documented in several companion documents.
 Before analyzing the impact of specific shocks we discuss general properties
 of the transmission mechanisms present in the model.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
First we describe the general response to demand shocks (Section 1.1), followed
 by similar considerations for supply shocks (Section 1.2 for shocks to labor
 supply and productivity, section 1.3 for shocks to foreign prices and section
 1.4 for financial shocks).
 After this we discuss how the financing of public expenditure affects the
 dynamic responses of the model (Section 1.5).
 Finally, we write briefly about the sectors in MAKRO.
 Given their large contribution to GDP it is often enough to look at the
 service and manufacturing sectors if one wants to understand the marginal
 properties of the model (Section 1.6).
 The individual shock analyzes are described in the subsequent sections.
